                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On June 8, 1953, Lieutenant <persName corresp="#p_HMGWKJ1">General William K.
                        Harrison</persName> and General <persName corresp="#p_NILG1">Nam
                        Il</persName> signed the agreement which established the “Terms of Reference
                    for the Neutral Nations Repatriation Commission” culminating 18 months of
                    negotiations over Item 4 of the armistice agenda. For text of the agreement, see
                    Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 22, 1953, pages
                    866–868.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
